====================================================================
====================================================================
ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW
====================================================================

Atlas is designed as a modular, conversation-first Autonomous AI
Operating System.

Each major platform component has a clearly defined responsibility while
working together through a unified execution model.

No subsystem should operate independently of the overall Atlas
architecture.

====================================================================

FOUNDATION LAYER

Provides the core infrastructure required for all Atlas capabilities.

Primary Components

• Authentication

• Inventor Workspace

• Journey Engine

• Persistent Data Model

• Conversation Interface

• Document Storage

• Executive Dashboard

====================================================================

INTELLIGENCE LAYER

Transforms inventor information into structured business knowledge.

Primary Components

• Executive Intelligence

• Evidence Intelligence

• Document Intelligence

• Engineering Intelligence

• Manufacturing Intelligence

• Patent Intelligence

Each intelligence system maintains a single authoritative knowledge
domain while sharing verified information with the rest of the platform.

====================================================================

EXECUTION LAYER

Coordinates autonomous work throughout Atlas.

Primary Components

• Autonomous Execution Engine

• Delegation Engine

• Conversation Orchestrator

• Founder Approval Engine

• Unified Action Queue

• Mission Control

The Execution Layer determines what work should occur, coordinates
departments, tracks execution progress, and advances work automatically
whenever authority permits.

====================================================================

KNOWLEDGE LAYER

Atlas continuously builds institutional knowledge.

Knowledge sources include:

• Founder conversations

• Uploaded documents

• Generated packages

• Engineering data

• Market research

• Validation results

• Executive decisions

Knowledge is persistent, reusable, evidence-backed, and continuously
improves future decision making.

====================================================================

FOUNDER EXPERIENCE LAYER

The founder interacts with Atlas through a single unified executive
experience.

Primary Surfaces

• Conversation

• CEO Command Center

• Executive Dashboard

• Mission Control

• Executive Briefings

Internal execution details remain hidden unless explicitly requested.

====================================================================

ARCHITECTURAL PRINCIPLES

Every future capability shall:

• Extend the existing architecture.

• Preserve modularity.

• Maintain a single source of truth.

• Reuse existing execution infrastructure.

• Integrate with Executive Intelligence.

• Improve founder outcomes.

Architectural consistency takes precedence over short-term convenience.

