CURRENT ACTIVE MILESTONE
====================================================================

Current Milestone

AT-018 — Founder Experience Simplification

Status

ACTIVE DEVELOPMENT

Priority

Highest

====================================================================

MISSION

Transform Atlas from an engineering-driven platform into a founder-first
operating system.

The underlying architecture is now sufficiently mature that future
development should focus on improving the founder experience rather than
building additional infrastructure.

Atlas should feel like hiring an experienced CEO—not operating a complex
software platform.

====================================================================

PRIMARY OBJECTIVES

The AT-018 milestone shall focus on the following objectives.

1. Simplify the Founder Experience

Reduce unnecessary complexity throughout the application.

Every screen should communicate only the information required for the
founder's next business decision.

--------------------------------------------------------------------

2. Hide Implementation Details

Execution engines,

queues,

workers,

internal orchestration,

dependency graphs,

execution contracts,

and technical implementation details should remain behind the scenes.

Atlas should communicate business outcomes rather than internal system
activity.

--------------------------------------------------------------------

3. Improve Executive Communication

Replace technical status messages with executive language.

Instead of describing what the software is doing internally, Atlas
should communicate:

• Completed

• Currently Working On

• Waiting

• Recommended Next Step

• Requires Founder Approval

--------------------------------------------------------------------

4. Reduce Founder Interruptions

Atlas should continue executing work whenever authority permits.

Founder interaction should occur only when required by the Authority
Boundaries defined within this Release Master Plan.

--------------------------------------------------------------------

5. Progressive Disclosure

Present information in layers.

The default experience should remain simple.

Additional technical detail should be available only when explicitly
requested.

--------------------------------------------------------------------

6. Create A CEO Experience

Every interaction should reinforce the feeling that Atlas is operating
the inventor's business rather than waiting for instructions.

====================================================================

SUCCESS CRITERIA

AT-018 will be considered complete when:

✓ The founder dashboard is significantly simplified.

✓ Duplicate executive messaging has been eliminated.

✓ Internal implementation terminology is hidden.

✓ Executive communication focuses on outcomes rather than processes.

✓ Founder interruptions are minimized.

✓ Atlas consistently behaves like an experienced executive.

====================================================================

NEXT MILESTONE

After successful completion of AT-018, development shall continue with
the next milestone defined in the Future Roadmap section of this
document.

