REVISION POLICY

This document is intended to evolve throughout the lifetime of Project
Atlas.

Future revisions shall update this document to reflect the current state
of the platform while preserving internal consistency and architectural
continuity.

When changes are made:

• Completed milestones shall move to the historical record.

• The current active milestone shall be updated.

• The future roadmap shall be revised as priorities evolve.

• Engineering directives shall remain aligned with product principles.

• Obsolete or conflicting information shall be removed rather than
  duplicated.

At all times, this document shall present one clear and authoritative
view of Project Atlas.

====================================================================

FINAL DECLARATION

Project Atlas exists to help inventors transform ideas into successful
products through trusted executive intelligence, autonomous execution,
and evidence-based decision making.

Every release should make Atlas:

• More autonomous.

• More intelligent.

• More capable.

• More trustworthy.

• Simpler for founders to use.

The success of Project Atlas will be measured not by the number of
features implemented, but by the measurable progress founders achieve
using the platform.

